message.content: Rosa arkansana, also known as prairie rose, is a species of shrub in the rose family. It is native to North America. The rose has pink to reddish-pink flowers that bloom in late spring or early summer. The leaves are pinnate and have serrated edges. The shrub can grow up to 6 feet tall and can spread up to 8 feet wide. The stems have sharp thorns. The fruit of the rose is a bright red or orange hip. The Rosa arkansana can be found in prairies, hillsides, and rocky bluffs.
